Description:
Permanent Home or Country Getaway at Clunes
Situated 1 kilometre to the Main Street in Clunes and 30 minutes to Ballarat is this low maintenance, north facing vinyl clad home with a front veranda and enjoying a great outlook to Mount Beckworth. The land area is approximately 3 acres and is fenced into 3 paddocks with an 80 metre long dog run and 4 dog kennels making it secure for your pets.
Services include town water, mains power, septic system and an unequipped bore which could feed the gardens. The home sits on concrete stumps and has an iron roof. There is a single garage with concrete floor, remote door and power plus a workshop area. Under the carport is a caravan which is included in the sale. The home features an L-shaped lounge and dining room with wood heater, high cathedral ceilings and a split system. The kitchen has been updated and features all gas cooking and instant gas hot water. The master bedroom is large in size, as is the bathroom. At the rear of the home is a sunroom plus an office or 2nd bedroom. Completing the package is a large laundry.

Description:
Natural Bush Setting with Large Shed
Presenting for your pleasure approximately 30 acres of natural bushland with abundant native wildlife. This parcel of land is far enough from suburbia to enjoy the peace and tranquillity of nature, yet close enough to town (Clunes) to duck in for groceries. The shed is approximately 14 x 7 mt, has a concrete floor and is partially lined with MDF boards. There is also a 40 shipping container for storage which will remain on site, as well as a quaint timber shed with a sunken pit in the centre. Roads have been cleared through the property for walking or driving and an unregistered 2WD vehicle will also be provided with the purchase for recreational use.
Power available and water tank installed to a tap.
Road boundary on three sides. Zoned Low Density Residential, so possible subdivision potential STCA. Entry is best via Cemetery Rd, then turn left at the pointer boards and follow the boundary.

Description:
Stunning Young Family Abode in Historic Clunes.
Are you looking for a quality home, with great proportions both inside and out? If yes then look no further. The attractive property with delightful gardens at front and rear also has a calming colour scheme throughout with earthy and neutral tones. The dwelling cries out for entertaining with vast living areas, a huge decking/pergola area and enough yard to host the 5th Ashes match. The bedrooms will all take your larger suites and the king size master has his & hers WIR and a twin vanity ensuite. All year comfort is had with combustion heating and two reverse cycle air-conditioners. The trades person will also appreciate the extra shedding.

Description:
1317M2 (0.32 Acres) Solid, Central Some New & Old
Within walking distance to the supermarket and primary school this highset and structurally sound home presents a rare opportunity with potential only limited by your imagination. Some period features join tasteful renovations including an enclosed breezeway leading to huge new bathroom (separate shower & bath), new laundry toilet. There are three good sized bedrooms; spacious open plan country kitchen and lounge share a historic central load bearing feature brick wall. Although liveable the remainder of the rooms are best described as a work in progress with re-plastering well underway with areas in need cosmetic attention only. Outside there are two GI sheds (workshop & wood), landscaped tiered gardens and possibly the most remarkable views over the football ground and township.
Insights: 27 Angus Street, CLUNES VIC 3370 was last sold in 2013.

Description:
Charming period home in hub of historic Clunes.
Don't miss this wondrous opportunity to secure a charismatic abode in the CBD of popular Clunes. The home overlooks the town's bowls club and parkland. A thirty second stroll has you visiting the shops of town or dining out. The three bedroom residence will surprise with large proportion throughout and sweet original character. All bedrooms will take your queen size suites and the formal lounge is spacious and handsome with an exceptional fireplace and double hung windows. The kitchen has a little old and new, with original cupboards, but with new stainless steel appliances and fresh bench-tops. The second bathroom has also seen much love, now delivering new big bathtub, vast separate shower and stone bench-top to the vanity. A rear porch could always be slightly altered to become a 2nd living area. The dwelling sits on a large allotment offering amazing potential. A lovely home, an exciting weekend or maybe let for a tidy return.
Insights: 19 Ligar Street, Clunes VIC 3370 was last sold in 2013 and 17 other 3 bedroom house in Clunes have recently been sold.
